\begin_layout Standard
In order to recover the FGR rate of the population decay, a straightforward
 means is that, we design the quantum transition for the electronic system
 as a population relaxation at the decay rate 
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
k_{R}\left(t\right)\equiv\kappa\left(1-\rho_{00}\left(t\right)\right)
\end{equation}

\end_inset

to complement Eq.
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset


\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand eqref
reference "eq:EOM_population_Ehrenfest"

\end_inset

.
 With this additional relaxation, the population dynamics follows
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
\frac{\partial}{\partial t}\rho_{11}\left(t\right)=-k_{Eh}\rho_{11}\left(t\right)-k_{R}\rho_{11}\left(t\right)=\kappa\rho_{11}\left(t\right).
\end{equation}

\end_inset

At time 
\begin_inset Formula $t$
\end_inset

, the additional decay rate 
\begin_inset Formula $k_{R}\left(t\right)$
\end_inset

 complement the Ehrenfest decay rate 
\begin_inset Formula $k_{Eh}\left(t\right)$
\end_inset

 to ensure the population dynamics follow the FGR decay rate.
 Note that the radiation filed is considered at zero temperature, so we
 exclude thermal transition from 
\begin_inset Formula $\left|0\right\rangle $
\end_inset

 to 
\begin_inset Formula $\left|1\right\rangle $
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Note Note
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
formal EOM
\end_layout

\end_inset

To formulate the complementary quantum transition formally, we write the
 equation of motion for the density matrix 
\begin_inset Formula $\rho\left(t\right)$
\end_inset

 in the form of 
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
\frac{\partial}{\partial t}\rho\left(t\right)=-\frac{i}{\hbar}\left[\widehat{H}^{\mathrm{el}},\rho\left(t\right)\right]+{\cal L}_{R}\left(t\right)\rho\left(t\right),\label{eq:EOM_Ehrenfest+R}
\end{equation}

\end_inset

with an additional super-operator term responsible for the complementary
 transition.
 The super-operator is given by
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
{\cal L}_{R}\rho=\left(\begin{array}{cc}
k_{R}\rho_{11} & \frac{1}{2}k_{R}\left(\frac{\rho_{11}}{\rho_{00}}-1\right)\\
\frac{1}{2}k_{R}\left(\frac{\rho_{11}}{\rho_{00}}-1\right) & -k_{R}\rho_{11}
\end{array}\right).
\end{equation}

\end_inset

Since there is no decoherence introduced, the off-diagonal element of 
\begin_inset Formula ${\cal L}_{R}\rho$
\end_inset

 is obtained by conversing the purity of density matrix.
 i.e.
 
\begin_inset Formula $\frac{d}{dt}(\tilde{\rho}_{11}\tilde{\rho}_{22}-\left|\tilde{\rho}_{12}\right|^{2})=0$
\end_inset

 
